procedure he maintained enhanced the sexual responses of a new mother, transforming her into "a horny little house mouse." Burt did so without first getting the consent of his patients. Yet he was allowed to practice for over thirty years, mutilating hundreds of women in the process. It would be easy to dismiss Dr. Burt as a monstrous aberration, a modern-day Dr. Frankenstein. Yet as medical historian Sarah Rodriguez reveals, that's not the whole story. The Love Surgeon asks tough questions about Burt's heinous acts and what they reveal about the failures of the medical establishment: How was he able to perform an untested surgical procedure? Why wasn't he obliged to get informed consent from his patients? And why did it take his peers so long to take action? The Love Surgeon is both a medical horror story and a cautionary tale about the limits of professional self-regulation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGenerative organsxSurgeryzOhioxHistory. 0aGynecologistszOhiovBiography. 0aSurgeonszOhiovBiography. 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / General.2bisacsh  aTrust, Harm, Love, Critical issues, Health, Medicine, History, Nursing, Health Policy, Public Health, Gender Studies, Women's Studies, General Interest, FITNESS, Obstetrics, Disease, Women Health, Gynecology, Health Issue, Medical, Ethics, Social Science, Janet Phillips, Regulation, Love Surgeon, Stock Assumptions, Surgical Development, Creepy Surgery, community reaction, Sarah Rodriguez, Medical Historian, Burt's heinous acts, surgical procedure.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020 Englishz9783110704808